3. Polymorphism:
What is polymorphism in Java?
a) The ability of a class to have multiple constructors
b) The ability of a method to have multiple implementations
c) The process of creating an object from a class
d) The ability of a class to have multiple instance variables


4.Abstraction:
What is abstraction in Java?
a) The process of creating an object from a class
b) The ability of a class to have multiple constructors
c) The bundling of data and the methods that operate on that data into a single unit
d) The process of hiding the implementation details of a class


5. Method Overriding:
What is method overriding in Java?
a) Creating a new method with the same name in a subclass
b) Creating a new method with a different name in a subclass
c) Modifying the implementation of a method in a superclass
d) Creating a static method in a subclass with the same name as a static method in a superclass


